ES-EKF Root Cause Analysis (Resolved)
======================================
ISSUE #1: IMU Topic Mismatch
  Before: /px4/imu (no publisher — was only visible as zombie ghost topic)
  After:  /fmu/out/sensor_combined (confirmed PUBLISHING by XRCE-DDS bridge)
  Status: FIXED in es_ekf_node.cpp parameter default

ISSUE #2: GNSS Topic Mismatch
  Before: /px4/gnss
  After:  /fmu/out/vehicle_gps_position
  Status: FIXED in es_ekf_node.cpp parameter default

ISSUE #3: QoS Durability Mismatch [ROOT CAUSE — FINAL FIX]
  PX4 Publisher QoS:
    Reliability:  BEST_EFFORT
    Durability:   TRANSIENT_LOCAL  ← key
    History:      UNKNOWN
  ES-EKF Subscriber QoS (BEFORE):
    Reliability:  BEST_EFFORT
    Durability:   VOLATILE  ← incompatible with TRANSIENT_LOCAL
  DDS Behaviour: VOLATILE subscriber SILENTLY receives ZERO messages from TRANSIENT_LOCAL publisher
  Fix Applied:   Changed subscriber QoS to BEST_EFFORT + TRANSIENT_LOCAL
  Status: FIXED in es_ekf_node.cpp — binary rebuilt 2026-03-01 12:09:19

Code Fix Applied (es_ekf_node.cpp)
====================================
  // PX4 XRCE-DDS publishes with BEST_EFFORT + TRANSIENT_LOCAL.
  // A VOLATILE subscriber silently receives nothing — QoS must match.
  auto px4_qos = rclcpp::QoS(rclcpp::KeepLast(10))
      .best_effort()
      .durability(rclcpp::DurabilityPolicy::TransientLocal);

  imu_sub_ = create_subscription<sensor_msgs::msg::Imu>(imu_topic, px4_qos, ...);
  gnss_sub_ = create_subscription<sensor_msgs::msg::NavSatFix>(gnss_topic, px4_qos, ...);

